href="markweber.xml"
addr="markweber"
title="Mark Weber">Mark Weber</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="venue">Applied Categorical Structures</fr:meta><fr:meta
name="doi">10.1007/s10485-007-9079-2</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A 2-categorical generalisation of the notion of elementary topos is provided, and some of the properties of the Yoneda structure (<fr:link
type="local"
href="street-walters-1978.xml"
addr="street-walters-1978"
title="Yoneda structures on 2-categories">Street and Walters, J. Algebra, 50:350–379, 1978</fr:link>) it generates are explored. Results enabling one to exhibit objects as cocomplete in the sense definable within a Yoneda structure are presented. Examples relevant to the globular approach to higher dimensional category theory are discussed. This paper also contains some expository material on the theory of fibrations internal to a finitely complete 2-category (<fr:link
type="local"
href="street-1974.xml"
addr="street-1974"
title="Fibrations and Yoneda’s lemma in a 2-category">Street, Lecture Notes in Math., 420:104–133, 1974</fr:link>) and provides a self-contained development of the necessary background material on Yoneda structures.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
